---
layout: base.njk
title: Web Everything — States
---

<section class="intro">
  <h1>States</h1>
  <p>
    States are <strong>standards for the state and validation layer</strong> — schemas, signals, and
    stores expressed declaratively over web primitives. Each state below links to its full specification.
  </p>
</section>

<div class="project-grid">
  {% for state in states %}
  {# #1870 (#1820 Fork 1a): <we-card> frame + status → <we-badge>; the .project-card frame is stripped by
     `.project-card:has(> we-card)` in style.css so the card is the sole frame.
     Status vocab: active→success, draft→info, concept→warning, else→neutral. #}
  {% set statusTone = 'success' if state.status == 'active' else ('info' if state.status == 'draft' else ('warning' if state.status == 'concept' else 'neutral')) %}
  {# #2169: overlay-link, not a wrapping <a>. A summary may carry authored inline links, and an <a> may not
     contain another <a> — a wrapping anchor makes the browser clone empty ghost tiles (see adapters.njk /
     component-render-build-hook.cjs renderProjectGrid). `.project-card:has(> we-card)` still strips the frame. #}
  <div class="project-card">
    <a href="/states/{{ state.id }}/" class="project-card-link" aria-label="View {{ state.name }}"></a>
    <we-card>
      <div class="project-header" style="margin-bottom: 0.75rem; display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: center; gap: 0.5rem;">
        <h3 class="project-title" style="margin: 0;">{{ state.name }}</h3>
        <we-badge tone="{{ statusTone }}">{{ state.status | title }}</we-badge>
      </div>
      <p style="margin: 0; color: var(--color-text-muted); font-size: 0.9em;">{{ state.summary | safe }}</p>
    </we-card>
  </div>
  {% endfor %}
</div>
